        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "The creation and maintenance of an environment that feels, and is safe, is of paramount importance to the patients, staff, and carers within the Trust's acute inpatient settings."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "Whilst none of the acute adult inpatient wards are classed as locked or secure wards, due to the majority of the patients being informal and therefore able to exercise their freedom of movement and leave the wards if they wish by using the door release button, there is a need to monitor, regulate and appropriately respond to who attends and accesses the inpatient wards. The Mental Health Code of Practice 2015 (8.57) states that \u201clocking doors, placing staff on reception to control entry to particular areas, and the use of electronic swipe cards, electronic key fobs and other technological innovations of this sort, are all methods that hospitals should consider to manage entry to and from clinical areas to ensure the safety of the service users and others\u201d."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Purpose"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "This policy sets out the requirements for the use of managed entry and exits to the acute hospital wards based on the guidance given in the Mental Health Act Code of Practice 2015, Chapter 8 and the Mental Capacity Act 2005."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "url": "MSEPO-21223 Access to wards policy.003.png"
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "This policy applies to the Trust's acute inpatient areas where doors may be locked in the circumstances set out in this procedure and to both informal and patients detained under the Mental Health Act who are on the adult inpatient wards."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Role and responsibilities within the Trust"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "Trust Board/Chief Executive"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The Trust has a responsibility to have effective risk management procedures in place, which maintain the rights and dignity of patients, and for the monitoring of these processes."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "Heads of Nursing and Matrons for the Adult Acute Inpatient wards"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The HoNs and Matrons are responsible for:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The implementation of the procedure and clinical staff compliance with its contents"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Reviewing the frequency of this procedures implementation"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Any staff they manage being aware of this procedure and its contents"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Keeping this procedure under review so that its contents are reflective of current practice"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.3,
                "text": "Clinical staff who work within the Acute Inpatient Wards The staff are responsible for:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Implementing the requirements of this procedure."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Reporting any none compliance with this procedure."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Procedure"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Acute Adult Inpatient Areas"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "ALL Acute Adult Inpatient areas will be locked between the hours of 22.00 and 07.00. Access to these wards by trust staff will be through key pad, swipe card or intercom."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "In the event of a medical emergency a member of the ward staff will be assigned to ensuring that there is ease of access for the responding clinical staff."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "When a decision may be made to lock the ward doors outside of the hours stipulated"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Whilst the Code of Practice 2015 does allow for a ward to be locked, within the Trust this would only be done in exceptional circumstances as it is an extreme measure which impinges on the freedom of movement for informal patients. In view of this, it should not be done without due consideration, consultation or exploration of alternative ways to deal with the situation and the decision to take such action can ONLY BE MADE BY THE NURSE IN CHARGE OF THE WARD and examples of when the locking of the ward doors may possibly be considered are:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Where any patient is considered to be a risk as defined by the Trust's risk management policy and procedure, the person in charge then has the responsibility to evaluate the defined risk and also consider the following, before locking the door for all or part of the shift:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The issues and risks which require the doors locking and any alternative to this course of action"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The benefits of locking the door"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The risks associated with the door being locked"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Why locking the door is the least restrictive option"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Following the return of an absconding patient to the ward, until such time that the multi-disciplinary team can assess the patients mental state"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "For the protection of staff and patients to prevent any person from entering the ward where it has been agreed by the multi- disciplinary team that the visitor has, or could have, a detrimental effect on the patients or staff in the area"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "NB: Restricting patients movement due to staff shortage is unacceptable and"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "should be brought to the attention of the relevant Matron immediately 5.2 Action to take once a decision has been made to lock the ward doors"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "All staff on duty must be informed of why this action was undertaken and the proposed time the doors will be locked."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A clear rationale must be established which demonstrates that the locking of the doors acts within the best interests of the patient(s)/carers/staff."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The assessments, consultation and decisions made must be fully documented in the patient's clinical record."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Full details of the incident/behaviour which led to the procedure being implemented must be recorded on the \u201cMonitoring Form for the Locking of Ward Doors\u201d Appendix 1"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The patients on the ward must be informed that the locked door procedure has been implemented, but that they may leave on request at any time, if this is appropriate."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 57
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A notice must be placed in full view that informs all patients/visitors that the locked door procedure has been implemented."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 58
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "An explanation at the earliest opportunity must be offered to the patient, and if appropriate, relative / carer why the ward doors were locked."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 59
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The Responsible Clinician or nominated deputy must be notified"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 60
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The nurse in charge must consider and review the patient's well- being, noting any immediate or potential change in their behaviour / mental state as a consequence of the locked doors and respond to this in a supportive and proactive manner."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 61
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A member of staff should be allocated to monitor the doors and take responsibility for allowing patients / visitors off the ward. The member of staff will also need to explain to any incoming visitors why the door has been temporarily locked."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 62
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "If the doors are expected to remain locked for more than half an hour an observation rota should be devised to enable staff to alternate at half hourly intervals."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 63
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "If the doors should remain locked for more than one shift the Ward Manager will review the situation, and inform the Matron. If this continues for more than three shifts, the ward manager will review again with the Matron."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 64
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "It remains the responsibility of the nurse in charge of each shift to review the need for the locked ward procedure to remain in place."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 65
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The service's Matron will audit the implementation of the Locked Door Procedure within their respective areas."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 66
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "Paediatric Inpatient Wards"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 67
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Paediatric Wards will be locked at all times."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 68
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Staff access to the wards is limited to those who need it, as outlined in the National Service Framework for Children"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 69
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Parents have 24hr access via intercom"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 70
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "General visiting between 12 midday and 8pm also via an intercom"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 71
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "Neonatal Intensive Care Unit"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 72
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Neonatal Intensive Care Unit will remain locked at all times"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 73
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Parents will be able to visit 24 hours along with other siblings"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 74
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Visiting details for other relatives/friends will be made available by the ward staff."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 75
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Training requirements"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 76
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "As a Trust procedure, all staff need to be aware of the key points that the procedure covers. Staff can be made aware through:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 77
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "A number of a variety of means such as;"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 78
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Team meetings."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 79
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Local Induction."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 80
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
